      <div class="subfield"><strong>$c - Time/date of action</strong> <div class="description">Concrete time or date of a future or past action.</div>
         <div class="description2">
            <div class="description">In conjunction with the appropriate action this may indicate date of accessioning,
                                 acquisition, classification, transfer, or description. The date and time are
                                 recorded according to <em>Representations of Dates and Times</em> (ISO 8601). The
                                 date requires 8 numeric characters in the pattern <em>yyyymmdd</em> (4 for the
                                 year, 2 for the month, and 2 for the day). The time requires 8 numeric characters
                                 in the pattern <em>hhmmss.f</em> (2 for the hour, 2 for the minute, 2 for the
                                 second, and 2 for a decimal fraction of the second, including the decimal point).
                                 The 24-hour clock (00-23) is used.
            </div>
         </div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
